"{\"uid\": \"rollingstone.com-music-music-lists-snoop-dogg-olympics-simone-biles-michael-phelps-1235071071\", \"text\": \"ByRolling Stone  Is anyone having a better time at the2024 Paris OlympicsthanSnoop Dogg?  The rapper has clearly been loving his duties as a special correspondent for NBC and he's already made the games way more fun for everyone involved. He's been busy hyping up athletes and rooting for Team USA, to the delight of fans watching at home. From swimming with Michael Phelps to carrying the torch at theopening ceremony,Snoop Dogg has stolen the show at just about every turn. Here are some of his best moments - and most hilarious - moments so far.  \\\"Snoop with a little French dog!\\\" \\\"SNOOP WITH A LITTLE FRENCH DOG!\\\" Is it stuck in your head yet? You are welcome. In a meet-cute for the ages captured by Access Hollywood, Snoop encountereda beret-bearing bulldogwhom he promptly named after couturier Pierre Cardin. \\\"He's spooned, he's groomed. He's dipped and whipped. And he's suited and booted,\\\" Snoopsaid, looking absolutely delighted. That's when he began the\\\"little French dog\\\"chant, while playing a mean game of keepaway avec Pierre and a diamond-white basketball.Beautiful.-S.V.L.  Simone BilesspottedSnoop first. The 38-time medalist was standing on the gymnastics floor during the qualifying round earlier this week when she suddenly gestured to her teammates and pointed into the audience. There was Snoop, hanging out in the stands in full dance-mode, arms outstretched and grooving. Within seconds, Jordan Chiles was right there with him, laughing and enjoying an impromptu dance party alongside Biles. It was just another example of the rapper building up the athletes and making the games that much more entertaining.-J.L.  \\u202aImagine looking up at the stands from the pool as you earn a gold medal and seeing an ecstatic Snoop Dogg clapping and cheering for you alongside your wife. That's what Caleb Dressel experienced after he competed in the Men's 4x100m freestyle relay and earned gold. \\\"Go baby, go!\\\" cheered Dressel's wife Meghan alongside Snoop. \\\"You got it, baby!\\\" screamed the rap star. \\\"Gold! Gold! Gold! Gold!\\\" He could've said the word eight times - that's how many gold medals Dressel has earned over his illustrious career. \\u202c-T.M.  One of the best things about Snoop's Olympics presence is that he seems game for anything, like this segment featuringswimming legend Michael Phelps. Saying he has the wingspan and \\\"lung power\\\" needed to excel, Snoop donned a cap and trunks and got in the pool with 23-time gold Olympic medal winner for a little lesson. Snoop may not have perfect form, but his sense of humor remained intact. \\\"Shout out to the Phelps family,\\\" he pants, \\\"and to the team that's going to give me some oxygen right now.\\\"-L.T.  The handling of the Olympic torch is reserved for icons of icons. Snoop's rap peers can boast about gaudy purchases and lucrative brand deals, but his time with the torch during the opening ceremony put him on hallowed ground. There was a time when he wasthe coverboyfor America's fear-mongering around hip-hop, but now he's among the world's most popular rappers, adding another bullet point to his accomplished career. The only way the moment would have been cooler is if he got to light up from the torch.-A.G.  Snoop joined Hoda Kotb for a quick interview with Simone Biles' parents, who caught the correspondents up on how the gymnast was feeling just before competing. Biles' mother shared that her daughter was excited that 17 of her family members had made it out to support her. Then she teased Snoop a little: She told him that he had met Biles years ago, though Snoop did not seem to remember. \\\"I will never forget that we met you in Times Square, 2010, \\\" she said. \\\" We asked for a picture - you said, 'Two minutes.' One, two, and you were gone!\\\" The story made Snoop immediately burst into laughter.-J.L.  Tennis star Coco Gauff, sadly, is not taking home an Olympic gold medal in women's singles, but she is leaving Paris with something else pretty rare and special:\\u00a0 anOlympic pinfrom Snoop, featuring the rapper standing near the Eiffel Tower blowing five circles of smoke resembling the Olympics rings into the air. \\\"Got something for you, beautiful. This is for you. Great game today. Go, USA,\\\" says Snoop, wearing a Gauff T-shirt, in a video posted on Instagram. Gauff responds: \\\"'Hey Mr Snoop. Thank you for this pin. This is the best pin.\\\" It may not be licensed by the IOCC, but betting this one is much sought-after by obsessive pin traders.-L.T.  Snoop Dogg, known for his chart-topping singles, tried out a new kind of track during the 2024 U.S. Olympic Trials. \\\"The Drop It Like It's Hot\\\" rapper competed in a 200m exhibition race, dressed in American flag sweatpants and a star-spangled shirt that paid homage to Kobe Bryant. Snoop had his work cut out for him, competing against four-time Olympic medallist Ato Bolden and two-time NCAA 200m champion Wallace Spearman. What started as a close race between Snoop and Spearman during the first stretch quickly became a blowout for the rapper. Snoop was just happy to have crossed the finish line: \\\"34.44 for a 52-year-old? Ain't bad.\\\"-K.R.  Snoop Dogg has always been celebrated for his flashy fashion sense, and the rap icon continues to serve up looks at the Olympics. But his best outfits so far have been the ones repping Team USA stars Simone Biles and Coco Gauff. For Gauff's tennis competition, Snoop sported a custom-made t-shirt with a large print of the Olympian. He pulled out all the stops for the GOAT Simone Biles:Underneath his official Olympics zip-up, Snoop's wore a t-shirt with the decorated gymnast beaming as she showed off all of her medals.-M.G.  Badminton might not seem like the coolest sport on the planet - a touch stuffy and old-fashioned, dare we say? But do not try telling that to Snoop Dogg. He was fully engaged when he got to join the broadcast team for a U.S.-China match. \\\"Oh, I love this badminton right here,\\\" tha Doggfather said. \\\"As you see, it do not stop 'til the casket drop. They are rockin' and rollin', back and forth.\\\" Then he narrated a rally in vivid play-by-play form: \\\"Gimme that. No, I need that. Nope, over here. Nope, over there. What about over there\\u2026 Nope, sit down. Wait a minute, hold on\\u2026. Get out the way! Move! I told you, we need that!\\\" OK, fine, we love badminton now too.-S.V.L.  Snoop has shown that he's down to enjoy any sport at the Games, and that includes the one where very special horses do their fancy little dances for everyone to admire. He and his bestie Martha Stewart were dressed to the nines for the dressage finals, looking ready to hop ontoTeam USA's famous \\\"rave horse\\\" Mopsieat a moment's notice. Luckily, no such acts of equestrian derring-do were needed - a good thing, since Snoop has admitted he'sscared of horses.-S.V.L.  Anyone watching Telemundo's broadcast of the 2024 Olympics got to see Snoop Dogg doing a side quest as he stopped by soccer commentator Andr\\u00e9s Cantor's booth at the USWMNT's match to learn how to yell \\\"GOOOOL!\\\" After showing off a bit of his Spanish, Snoop joined Cantor for a goal celebration. \\\"He gotta hold that thang too long,\\\" Snoop joked to the sports announcer. Cantor gifted Snoop with a custom Team USA soccer jersey and an invite to join him at the 2026 World Cup. \\\"I will be there!\\\" Snoop confirmed.-T.M.  What happens when you let Snoop Dogg into the Louvre after hours? He starts snooping around. As part of his correspondent duties, the rapper got a tour of the famed museum and went from object to object, bantering with his guide. He scoped out a painting that depicted what he thought was two women in bed, until his guide corrected him and told him one of the figures was the Greek god Cupid. \\\"Cupid, I knew it was somebody I knew,\\\" he quipped. The best part was when he got to the Mona Lisa and moved from side to side to see if the she followed him with her eyes. \\\"She smile real hard when I stand on this side,\\\" he joked.-J.L.  Contributors:Andre Gee,Maya Georgi,Julyssa Lopez,Tom\\u00e1s Mier,Kalia Richardson,Lisa Tozzi,Simon Vozick-Levinson  We want to hear it. Send us a tip using our anonymous form.  Rolling Stone is a part of Penske Media Corporation. \\u00a9 2026 Rolling Stone, LLC. All rights reserved.\"}"